### Remaining Concerns
- The intro's "chess board his father set up at his elementary school" and the chess section's "founded the team at Joe's elementary school in Fremont, California" cover nearly the same beat back-to-back. Not a cohesion break, but a small echo. The second-pass notes already tightened the closing chess-board phrasing; the intro/chess overlap is what's left, and trimming it would be a voice/tightening call, not a cohesion one.
- The closing section enters cold on the mother's death by design. If a reader feels that jolt, it's working as intended — the piece earns the abruptness by having held the daughters' integration register one paragraph earlier.
